1
00:00:01,752 --> 00:00:04,129
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:28,797
MAKESHIFT

3
00:01:29,381 --> 00:01:31,758
[Ooi]
Well then, let's begin tonight's meeting.

4
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:35,304
[Light] There's supposed to be eight
of them, but only seven are present.

5
00:01:35,387 --> 00:01:36,388
That must mean that...

6
00:01:36,555 --> 00:01:38,515
[L] They probably killed one
of their members.

7
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,683
[Soichiro] Hmm...

8
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,311
[Ooi] In order to further the growth
of the Yotsuba Group

9
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:46,023
and best serve its financial interests,
who should we kill next?

10
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:47,065
[all gasp]

11
00:01:47,149 --> 00:01:49,318
You see? It's just like I told you
last week!

12
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:51,903
[L] This is not good. At this rate...

13
00:01:52,279 --> 00:01:53,614
[Ooi] But before we get to that,

14
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:56,366
there are several topics
that we need to discuss.

15
00:01:56,575 --> 00:01:59,161
First, there is the issue
of Hatori's death.

16
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:00,662
[Namikawa] That was unavoidable.

17
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:04,833
To be honest, in a certain sense,
I'm relieved that Hatori's dead.

18
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,545
Kira has demonstrated that we must
be committed to these meetings.

19
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,423
We now know what will happen
if we try to leave.

20
00:02:11,715 --> 00:02:12,674
[Ooi grunts softly]

21
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:16,928
I think we all understand what Hatori's
death means for the rest of us.

22
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:18,972
Let's not take it lightly.

23
00:02:19,473 --> 00:02:22,684
Now, moving on. Our next topic
is Eraldo Coil's report…

24
00:02:22,809 --> 00:02:23,727
[all gasp]

25
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:27,022
One of their members just died
and that's all they're going to say?

26
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:32,069
So did we really pay five million dollars
for this report?

27
00:02:34,738 --> 00:02:36,490
I mean, come on. Look at this.

28
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:40,369
He hasn't found out anything important
about L like his name or his face.

29
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:43,372
Is this Coil guy seriously going
to be of any use to us?

30
00:02:43,497 --> 00:02:44,706
Hold on a second.

31
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:48,543
There is something very interesting
in the last part of this report.

32
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:52,714
Coil's warning us that we can't afford
to take L's existence too lightly.

33
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:57,636
In particular, it says, "The concentration
of killings that are beneficial to Yotsuba

34
00:02:57,761 --> 00:02:59,388
will likely be noticed by L

35
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:02,391
if they continue on Fridays
and Saturdays."

36
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:10,190
Sounds like this Eraldo Coil
has figured out what we've been up to.

37
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,942
I admit, it's quite impressive.

38
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:16,196
At any rate, I personally think
we should stop killing every weekend.

39
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:21,034
This is unbelievable. It's like they're
trying to confess to everything.

40
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:24,121
Hmm, as long as we have this video
as evidence,

41
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,081
we could probably arrest
all seven of them.

42
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,458
[L] This is not good.

43
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:31,545
Kira hasn't been flexible
up till now, has he?

44
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:34,673
It would be nice if he could spread out
his killings over the whole week.

45
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:37,718
The fact that Coil noticed
what we've been up to

46
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:40,929
makes it dangerous to continue killing
at our usual pace.

47
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:43,181
From now on,
we have to be even more careful

48
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:46,560
and make sure that nobody else happens
to notice a trend in these deaths.

49
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:48,979
Now, onto the main topic.

50
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:52,774
Who should we kill?

51
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:53,942
[Soichiro sighs]

52
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:58,447
I think we should focus on ELF Insurance.

53
00:03:58,822 --> 00:04:00,907
If they expand into the Japanese market,

54
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:04,369
Yotsuba and many other companies
will lose valuable clients to them.

55
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:05,620
[Higuchi] Agreed.

56
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:10,459
Alright. Any objections to killing these
people from ELF with accidental deaths?

57
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:11,793
[all] No objections.

58
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:13,712
-Ah.
-Is this for real?

59
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:15,881
How can they do this so easily?

60
00:04:16,131 --> 00:04:19,259
[Ooi] Another potential candidate
is Sentara Zenzai,

61
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:20,761
a member of the Kugisawa Group.

62
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:24,055
He's been protesting
Yotsuba's resort development plans.

63
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:26,516
Zenzai's known to have
high blood pressure,

64
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,144
so we can designate a time
for him to suffer a stroke,

65
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,563
resulting in natural death.
Any objections?

66
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:33,482
-[Yotsuba Group] No objections.
-[gasps]

67
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:36,443
Kira? Deaths by accident? By disease?

68
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,320
Designated times of death?

69
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:42,240
It's all just as we suspected.
We were right.

70
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:46,578
No. Unfortunately, we can only be
completely sure

71
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,580
after those people they've named are dead.

72
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:49,706
[both gasp]

73
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,833
[L] We will continue
to monitor these meetings

74
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:55,170
and take note of what they say,
how they act, and most importantly,

75
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,214
whether the people they choose
actually die.

76
00:04:57,839 --> 00:05:01,259
If we can confirm the connection
between their plans and the deaths,

77
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:04,137
then we'll definitely be able
to catch Kira.

78
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:06,181
-[both] Ryuzaki!
-[L grunts]

79
00:05:06,765 --> 00:05:09,226
What is it? There's no need
to yell in unison.

80
00:05:09,351 --> 00:05:12,062
I can't carry on
knowing these people will die!

81
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:13,939
-That's just immoral!
-Right.

82
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,440
[L] Here it comes.

83
00:05:15,524 --> 00:05:18,193
I know you're planning to catch Kira
by letting these guys

84
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:22,030
actually carry out these murders,
but... we can't let that happen!

85
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:25,992
That's right. It's obvious that these
seven men are behind the killings.

86
00:05:26,368 --> 00:05:29,412
With Matsuda's testimony
and this footage we've recorded,

87
00:05:29,538 --> 00:05:30,872
we have all the evidence.

88
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:33,625
[L] You're making this difficult.

89
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:37,921
If we were to take action now,
everything we've done would go to waste.

90
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:42,008
[Ooi] So, what do you say we take care
of the ELF in three weeks,

91
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:45,804
and as for Zenzai, we'll ask Kira
to kill him this weekend?

92
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:47,013
[all] No objections.

93
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:50,267
If that's what they're going to do,
then there's not much time left.

94
00:05:50,851 --> 00:05:54,646
Light, we already know the phone numbers
of these board members, don't we?

95
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:55,647
Yeah.

96
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:57,357
I don't care who we call.

97
00:05:57,524 --> 00:06:00,652
I need to reach one of these men
and have them stop these murders.

98
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:01,945
[L] Please, hold on.

99
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,281
That would cause suspicion.

100
00:06:04,656 --> 00:06:07,033
It would mean the investigation
caught up to them

101
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,870
three days after they were contacted
by Aiber.

102
00:06:10,662 --> 00:06:14,875
Also, it would make it far more unlikely
that we would be able to discover

103
00:06:14,958 --> 00:06:16,543
who the real Kira might be.

104
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:20,338
We can't afford such a huge setback
seeing how far we've come.

105
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:22,132
[slurping]

106
00:06:24,593 --> 00:06:26,219
In order to catch Kira…

107
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:28,972
we're going to need some solid proof.

108
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:37,022
Ryuzaki, if one of these seven men
is in fact Kira,

109
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:39,941
would it be safe to say that if I tried
calling one of them,

110
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:43,445
the odds of that person actually being
Kira is going to be one in seven?

111
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:46,698
I'm thinking there could be more
than one Kira among them.

112
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:49,034
A probability of two in seven at most.

113
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,703
If we're prepared to let them know
that the investigation

114
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:53,246
is catching up to them...

115
00:06:53,788 --> 00:06:55,582
let's place our bets on these odds.

116
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:59,085
Ryuzaki, I'm going to pose as L.

117
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:02,923
And judging from their conversation
so far, the one least likely to be Kira

118
00:07:03,006 --> 00:07:04,758
but with the most influence is...

119
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:06,843
-[L and Light] Namikawa.
-[Matsuda] Is Ooi!

120
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,011
[Matsuda groans]

121
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,764
[L] If you're going to make a call,
please use this phone.

122
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:13,308
It's set up, so it can't be traced
or tapped.

123
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:18,897
[Higuchi] You know, this would all go
a lot faster if we kill off the execs

124
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:21,066
of our rival companies
and be done with it.

125
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:23,151
[Mido] That would be going
a little too far.

126
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:24,194
CALL FROM ANONYMOUS

127
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:26,321
[Higuchi] Why? We could kill them
and split their holdings.

128
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,073
[Light's voice distorted]
Is this Reiji Namikawa,

129
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,908
head of the Yotsuba Group's
Marketing Department?

130
00:07:29,991 --> 00:07:32,786
Hmm. Yes, and who is this?

131
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,164
[Light] Listen carefully,
but don't draw attention to yourself.

132
00:07:36,498 --> 00:07:37,707
I am L.

133
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:38,667
[gasps]

134
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:44,714
[Light] I've planted cameras and wiretaps
around that meeting room.

135
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:47,884
Even as I speak, I'm recording footage
of your entire meeting.

136
00:07:48,218 --> 00:07:50,929
The first thing you discussed
was Hatori's death.

137
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,765
Now you're debating who to kill next.

138
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:55,392
Am I correct?

139
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:57,978
[Namikawa] He's been watching everything!

140
00:07:58,353 --> 00:08:00,063
If you are not Kira,

141
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:03,650
or if you are not someone
who can contact Kira directly,

142
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,360
let's make a deal.

143
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:06,653
[Namikawa] A deal?

144
00:08:07,404 --> 00:08:10,281
[L] I need you to delay the deaths
of ELF's president

145
00:08:10,365 --> 00:08:12,367
and Mr. Zenzai by one month.

146
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:16,121
I doubt it will be difficult for someone
of your standing to accomplish that.

147
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:20,166
[Namikawa] Yes, yes, I see.
Right. Go on.

148
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,127
[Light] If you complete your end
of the deal

149
00:08:22,252 --> 00:08:25,046
and cooperate with our requests
from now on, then your crimes--

150
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,508
No, not just yours, but everyone's crimes
with the exception of Kira

151
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:31,594
will be parked, based on the premise
that Kira blackmailed you

152
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:33,763
into participating in these meetings.

153
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:35,306
I see. Okay.

154
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:38,059
[Namikawa] My only option is to join L.

155
00:08:38,143 --> 00:08:40,895
No, I'll be dead if Kira manages
to find out.

156
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:42,397
What should I do?

157
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:46,067
If you tell the others about this call,
they will panic.

158
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,028
It would be no advantage to you.

159
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,238
Everyone would be arrested immediately.

160
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:52,073
But that's not my intention.

161
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:54,659
I'm planning to go one on one
against Kira.

162
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:59,372
Listen. If I win against Kira,
you'll be acquitted of all charges.

163
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:03,084
If Kira wins, then you'll be free
to carry on with your comfortable life.

164
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:08,089
Just play along with both parties.
Staying on the sidelines will be best.

165
00:09:08,506 --> 00:09:12,927
You're not in a position to lose anything
regardless of who wins in the end.

166
00:09:13,595 --> 00:09:17,515
You would only be at a loss if I decided
to arrest you right here and now.

167
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:20,727
[Namikawa] Damn it. He already knew
what answer I would've given.

168
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:23,438
[Light] That's all for now.

169
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,356
Right. I'll see you Monday, then.

170
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,652
What's going on, Namikawa?
Who was that?

171
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:33,698
One of my men screwed up again.
I'll have to fix it on Monday.

172
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:37,744
Anyway, sorry for the interruption.
Let's get back on topic.

173
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:42,791
We were discussing when we should kill
Zenzai and the men from ELF.

174
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,667
Here's what I'm thinking.

175
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:47,837
We'll give Coil one month
to reveal L's identity.

176
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:50,381
If he still hasn't uncovered
the information we need,

177
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:53,093
then we can go ahead
and kill the targets randomly.

178
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:57,680
Then, we'll give him another month
to investigate and repeat the process.

179
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:59,390
Once we get rid of L permanently,

180
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:02,060
we can go back to killing
two or three people a week.

181
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:06,648
In other words, our top priority
should be the elimination of L.

182
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:07,857
I see.

183
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:11,194
Once we kill L, there won't be anything
standing in our way.

184
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:13,613
But until then, we need to be careful.

185
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:16,407
Right. Sounds like a reasonable plan
to me.

186
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:20,078
We need to be extremely careful
if we don't wanna get caught.

187
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:23,123
[Ooi] Then we're in agreement.
We'll give Coil one month.

188
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:24,541
[Yotsuba Group] Agreed.

189
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,419
[Namikawa] L, this should satisfy you
for now.

190
00:10:28,545 --> 00:10:32,006
[Ooi] We'll still be meeting
on a weekly basis. That is all.

191
00:10:32,257 --> 00:10:33,341
[L] That went well.

192
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:34,759
[Light] Yeah.

193
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:37,262
You really are quite amazing, Light.

194
00:10:37,512 --> 00:10:40,098
Not only did you manage
to delay the killings,

195
00:10:40,265 --> 00:10:43,309
but you also set up Namikawa
as a potential mole for us.

196
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:46,479
Sounded exactly like the sort of thing
I would do.

197
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:48,565
And you thought of it quicker than I did.

198
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:51,943
At this rate…

199
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:55,155
if I end up dying somehow,

200
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:58,616
it's quite possible that you would be
capable of succeeding me.

201
00:10:58,783 --> 00:11:00,994
What? Why are you being so morbid?

202
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:05,081
There isn't time for that. We only have
a month to figure out Kira's identity

203
00:11:05,165 --> 00:11:06,916
and gather evidence against him
to prove it.

204
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,376
This is only the beginning.

205
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:10,128
[L] Yes…

206
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:14,132
But you were the one who first noticed
the connection between Yotsuba and Kira.

207
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:16,759
You actually might be more capable
than I am.

208
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:20,221
I honestly believe you could take this on.

209
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:21,431
[gasps]

210
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:24,350
[L] Tell me. If I should die…

211
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:27,020
would you take over from me as L?

212
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:28,897
Huh...

213
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:55,048
[L] If I should die,
would you take over for me as L?

214
00:11:57,759 --> 00:12:01,763
If he is Kira and just playing innocent,
he's sure to say yes.

215
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:03,556
What are you talking about?

216
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:07,393
As long as we're joined by these,
we would die together anyway.

217
00:12:09,646 --> 00:12:10,688
I see.

218
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:15,777
Ryuzaki, I'm sorry,
but I'm gonna have to tell everyone

219
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:18,071
-what you're really thinking right now.
-[Matsuda gasps]

220
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:21,574
[Light] He thinks that if I am Kira,
then there are two possibilities.

221
00:12:21,658 --> 00:12:24,285
I'm either just pretending I'm not him
and putting on an act,

222
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:27,705
or that Kira's power has passed on
from me to someone else,

223
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:30,917
and I have no memory
that I was ever Kira in the first place.

224
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,836
He's trying to determine which,
if either, is the truth.

225
00:12:34,504 --> 00:12:37,632
The first theory,
if I am putting on an act,

226
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:40,134
he will never remove these handcuffs.

227
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:43,638
No, even if it wasn't pretending
to be innocent,

228
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:48,184
I'm sure he still wouldn't take them off.
Ryuzaki still believes that I'm Kira.

229
00:12:48,518 --> 00:12:51,062
Even if that power had been passed
to someone else,

230
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,563
he thinks that I would have planned

231
00:12:52,689 --> 00:12:55,483
to have it return to me once I'm safe
from suspicion.

232
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:59,362
In other words,
I wasn't being controlled at all.

233
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:01,531
He thinks it was a plan,

234
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:05,451
to pass on the power and arrange for it
to come back to me once I'd been cleared.

235
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:10,415
[L] Impressive. You figured out exactly
what I'd been thinking all this time.

236
00:13:10,832 --> 00:13:13,960
[Light] Ryuzaki's theory
is that once I steal L's title,

237
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:16,296
I will become Kira again.

238
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,089
[L] Correct.

239
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:22,552
[Light] Taking on the identity of L,
having the power to control the police

240
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:25,263
in every country
while being Kira in secret...

241
00:13:25,847 --> 00:13:27,056
It's ideal.

242
00:13:27,974 --> 00:13:31,894
And you're thinking I could do it.
No, that I would do it.

243
00:13:32,103 --> 00:13:33,604
That's what you're saying, isn't it?

244
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:34,897
[L] Yes.

245
00:13:35,315 --> 00:13:36,983
[Light breathes sharply]
But what about now?

246
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:39,902
I told you, I don't want your title.
That should prove, even to you,

247
00:13:39,986 --> 00:13:41,863
that I'm not putting on an act,
shouldn't it?

248
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:46,909
[L] If this is all an act
and you are trying to steal my identity,

249
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:50,913
there's no chance you'd be foolish enough
to reveal your plan in front of everyone.

250
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:52,373
-Wouldn't you agree?
-[Light exhales]

251
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:53,958
[Light] Ryuzaki…

252
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:56,586
Huh?

253
00:13:57,086 --> 00:14:01,341
Do you think that I'm actually capable
of becoming a murderer?

254
00:14:01,716 --> 00:14:02,592
Kira?

255
00:14:03,301 --> 00:14:05,053
Even after I helped you catch him?

256
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,139
Do I seem like that kind of person to you?

257
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:16,230
[L] Yes, you do. I've always thought so.

258
00:14:16,898 --> 00:14:18,024
[both gasp]

259
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,323
[groans] Not again!

260
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:27,825
Okay, break it up! Once is enough!

261
00:14:27,909 --> 00:14:30,703
It was a draw, so let's just leave it
as an even match, okay?

262
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:32,288
[sighs] Yeah, you're right.

263
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:36,167
Anyway, let's focus on catching
the Kira that's in front of us right now.

264
00:14:36,501 --> 00:14:39,337
As long as I have the handcuffs on,
you shouldn't have any complaints.

265
00:14:39,462 --> 00:14:43,132
I suppose so. We only have a month,
so there's no time to get distracted.

266
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:44,217
[Matsuda sighs in relief]

267
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,469
-Ryuzaki...
-Yes?

268
00:14:47,095 --> 00:14:49,097
[Soichiro] We have plenty
of footage from this meeting.

269
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:51,474
Can't we use that as evidence
against those seven men

270
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:53,643
and prevent the murders
of other criminals?

271
00:14:53,768 --> 00:14:55,436
[L] Here we go again.

272
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:58,147
-Unfortunately, no.
-But why?

273
00:14:58,231 --> 00:15:01,734
At the moment, we're not certain
if Kira is among those seven men.

274
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:03,945
If all they have
is a tenuous connection with him,

275
00:15:04,028 --> 00:15:06,781
then Kira will kill them
as soon as they're arrested.

276
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:09,700
We have to be absolutely sure
that Kira is among them,

277
00:15:09,826 --> 00:15:12,120
so there's no point in detaining them now.

278
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:14,080
And even if it does turn out
to be one of them,

279
00:15:14,205 --> 00:15:17,375
it will still be quite difficult
to determine who the culprit is.

280
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:20,920
Hmm, I believe it's still far too early
for us to make our move.

281
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:25,425
Hold on. At the same time, we can't say
that he's definitely not among the seven.

282
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:27,593
That means there's a chance
the killings will stop

283
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,929
if we take this opportunity
to arrest them.

284
00:15:30,263 --> 00:15:33,808
I think Dad's right. There is a chance.
We have to act on it.

285
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:38,938
Excuse me, but I think from now on,
I should go after Kira by myself.

286
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:39,939
[Light] Huh?

287
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:42,275
You can use these headquarters,
as you wish.

288
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,986
I'll also be here,
but we will be working independently.

289
00:15:45,236 --> 00:15:47,989
You can conduct your investigation
under your own direction.

290
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,740
Feel free to arrest those men if you like.

291
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:52,493
I will be carrying on
my own investigation.

292
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:55,955
We'll only get into arguments if we don't
split up and act separately at this point.

293
00:15:56,122 --> 00:15:57,540
This is for the best.

294
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:59,333
[Soichiro] Are you saying
you're going to figure out

295
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:01,627
who Kira is by any means necessary?

296
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:06,257
[L] Yes. This case will never be solved
unless we capture Kira himself.

297
00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:10,178
Don't get me wrong. I wouldn't say
that preventing deaths is pointless.

298
00:16:11,888 --> 00:16:15,141
But if we don't uncover the entire truth,
once and for all,

299
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:19,645
Kira will only appear again and the number
of victims will continue to increase.

300
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:24,400
That's why I believe it's more important
to try and find out who Kira really is.

301
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:28,070
As I've been saying,
I'm opposed to arresting those seven men.

302
00:16:28,196 --> 00:16:31,616
If you want to do so, then you will have
to take responsibility for it.

303
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:33,826
I will pursue Kira on my own.

304
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,995
We only have one month.

305
00:16:37,038 --> 00:16:38,831
I wonder who will succeed.

306
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:42,001
[stammering] Ryuzaki. Where are you going?

307
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:43,252
[L] To Amane's room.

308
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:45,630
Sorry, I know you're on your father's side
in all this,

309
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:47,632
but I can't remove these handcuffs.

310
00:16:47,757 --> 00:16:49,800
I'm afraid you're gonna have
to come along with me.

311
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:56,390
[Misa humming]

312
00:16:57,475 --> 00:16:58,518
[door opening]

313
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:02,063
[gasps] Light! I didn't know we were
supposed to have a date!

314
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:03,231
Oh, right. I should have known.

315
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,900
-Misa Amane.
-[Light grunts]

316
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:08,027
Tell me, do you love Light
from the bottom of your heart?

317
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:08,986
Huh?

318
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:13,908
-Yeah! Of course I do.
-But you also worship Kira, don't you?

319
00:17:14,242 --> 00:17:15,451
Well, yeah...

320
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:18,246
So, then. If you had to choose
between Light and Kira,

321
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:19,747
-who would you pick?
-What?

322
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:22,333
That's obvious.
Of course it's gonna be Light.

323
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:25,378
I'm really grateful to Kira and want
to meet him someday in person,

324
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:28,756
but that's not true love.
I definitely choose Light.

325
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:31,008
But your precious Light is planning
to catch Kira.

326
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,134
Isn't that right?

327
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:35,221
-Well yes, of course I am.
-[Misa yelps]

328
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:38,432
He says he wants to catch Kira.
Now what will you do?

329
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:42,270
Well, if that's what Light says,
then I'm gonna support him no matter what.

330
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:43,604
[L] I see.

331
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:47,358
So, if you were given the opportunity
to work with Light on this investigation,

332
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:49,485
-would you take the offer?
-What? Ryuzaki--

333
00:17:49,569 --> 00:17:53,030
Yeah! Of course I would.
I'd do anything I could to help Light!

334
00:17:53,114 --> 00:17:55,533
Wait. Hold on a second.
Where are you going with this?

335
00:17:55,825 --> 00:17:58,786
[L] I'm planning to have Aiber
pose as Eraldo Coil again.

336
00:17:58,953 --> 00:18:01,789
He'll tell the Yotsuba members
that while he was investigating L,

337
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:04,500
he discovered that Misa Amane
might know who he is.

338
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:07,336
He'll also tell them that L brought her
in for questioning

339
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,130
on the suspicion that she was
the second Kira.

340
00:18:09,589 --> 00:18:11,132
[Misa] That part is true.

341
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:15,011
If the Yotsuba Group believes that Misa
could be their lead to finding L,

342
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:16,846
then they'll say
that they want to meet her

343
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:18,848
to discuss their advertising campaign.

344
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:21,017
They'll use that opportunity
to question her.

345
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:24,687
Thanks to Matsuda's screw up,
they may already be considering Misa

346
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:27,148
as their new spokesperson,
so this could work.

347
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:28,482
Yeah. Right.

348
00:18:28,608 --> 00:18:30,818
-We can't do that.
-Why not?

349
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:33,487
This plan is too risky.
Who knows what could happen to you?

350
00:18:33,613 --> 00:18:37,491
[gasps] Oh, wow. Does that mean
you're worried about me? Yay!

351
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:41,245
But don't worry.
I won't mind doing something like this

352
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,455
if it's for you, Light.

353
00:18:43,039 --> 00:18:46,667
Listen, Misa. If they suspect
that you might know who L really is,

354
00:18:47,001 --> 00:18:50,046
we don't know how far they'll be willing
to go to get that information.

355
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:54,216
No problemo. I promise I won't
say anything, even if they torture me.

356
00:18:54,342 --> 00:18:55,676
I can attest to that.

357
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:59,138
But Kira can control his victim's actions
before their death.

358
00:18:59,305 --> 00:19:01,474
There's a good chance
he might try to manipulate her

359
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:03,309
into revealing what she knows
and then kill her.

360
00:19:03,434 --> 00:19:07,313
Also, if he does manage to kill L,
he won't have any use for Misa.

361
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,773
He'd kill her to keep her silent.

362
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:10,316
I don't like the sound of that.

363
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:11,859
-[L] Light.
-Hmm?

364
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:15,988
You forget that if we win against Kira,
Misa won't die.

365
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:20,785
Besides, as long as we're handcuffed
together, you and I share the same fate.

366
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:23,996
If I die, so will you.

367
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,164
[Misa whimpers]

368
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:28,125
[L] If that happens, Misa is the one
who would grieve most of all.

369
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:32,296
Either we lose and both die together,
or we successfully catch Kira.

370
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:33,506
Which is it?

371
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:37,343
We catch Kira! I would never dream
about living in a world without Light.

372
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:40,429
-Yes, that would be dark.
-Cut it out. This is just crazy.

373
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:43,474
We're running out of time
and I'm starting to get desperate.

374
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:48,396
As for Misa Amane, I've turned to her
because I know her bravery

375
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,231
and love for you is boundless.

376
00:19:50,815 --> 00:19:52,316
Do you really mean it?

377
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:56,946
Oh, no. I think I've totally
misunderstood you all this time.

378
00:19:57,071 --> 00:19:58,739
I even called you a pervert.

379
00:19:59,073 --> 00:20:01,867
But you actually do understand
how I feel, don't you?

380
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:06,747
Yes. Misa is indisputably the most perfect
and worthy woman for Light.

381
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:08,374
Yay!

382
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,627
You're such a sweetie. Thank you, Ryuzaki.

383
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:13,379
I could actually fall for you.

384
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,381
[Misa] Let's not go that far.

385
00:20:15,798 --> 00:20:18,759
But you could maybe be a friend of mine.
Would that be okay?

386
00:20:19,677 --> 00:20:22,471
Yes. So now I've gained
yet another friend.

387
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:28,602
Yeah! Of course, any friend of Light's
is a friend of mine as well. [laughs]

388
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:32,815
-Let's all be friends together!
-[L] Yay, fun...

389
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:36,026
And of course, I would never think
of betraying any of my friends.

390
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:38,988
With our powers combined,
we'll arrest Kira!

391
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:40,614
-[L] Unfortunately...
-Huh?

392
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,950
Light's taking a different
investigative approach from us

393
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,077
and will be working with his father
and the others.

394
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:47,663
-[Light] Huh?
-[L] I'm afraid it'll just be you and I.

395
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:49,373
Huh? What's up with that?

396
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:51,834
Come on, L, now you're just playing dirty.

397
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:54,336
You're leaving me with no other choice
but to join your--

398
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,796
[L] No, that's quite all right.

399
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:58,674
[Misa] What are you talking about?
Of course he'll be joining us!

400
00:20:58,883 --> 00:21:00,217
That's not it either.

401
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,845
I've been opposed to this investigation
since the beginning.

402
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:05,514
-It's too dangerous for her.
-Oh, Light…

403
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:08,517
You're so sweet.
Thank you for worrying about me.

404
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:12,354
But please let me do this.
I wanna be useful to you somehow.

405
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:15,816
If I can be useful,
then maybe you'll love me even more.

406
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:20,488
And besides, I would gladly die
if it were for you, Light.

407
00:21:20,905 --> 00:21:23,199
[Soichiro] Figuring out the logistics
of arresting seven people

408
00:21:23,324 --> 00:21:27,036
is going to be challenging.
I don't suppose you two have any ideas?

409
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:28,788
Mogi? Matsuda?

410
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:32,458
TO BE CONTINUED

411
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:42,009
[theme music playing]
